caption: Their website, Google hours and when you call and get the automated message says they are open every day until 11 pm. Apparently on Sundays they close at 10 and the kitchen is closed at 9. They should update this so they don’t continue to steer customers incorrectly.
This place is incredible. We found it on a walk around downtown and found a gem. The food was beyond delicious and reasonably priced. The staff was great and the atmosphere was cozy and comfortable.
Awesome place!

Dakota was our server and helped make great recommendations. The cheese board was incredible and the make your own features was unique and fun. Great selection of beers and wonderful local options. Great date night spot!

Fabulous food, excellent service and so many wine and beer options! Montana was our server and she was a delight. Very helpful in making food and drink selections. Our family went on our first night in St. Louis and was a perfect start to our vacation.

The atmosphere was very nice and relaxing. I went alone and was seated immediately. I ordered the pretzel bites as an appetizer. They were decent but there is nothing amazing about them.  I ordered the pork for my main course. On the menu it is described as a "Brined bone-in chop, cherry chutney, wild rice with asparagus and bell pepper". When my food arrived there was no cherry chutney, half of my wild rice to burt/hard, and there was not q bell pepper in sight.  I asked my waitress about the chutney. She told me they where TAKING it off of the menu so they are no longer making it. That is information that should have been relayed upon my ordering of the pork chop. Not to mention it is still printed on the menu. She did go to the kitchen and get me a bowl of the chutney which I then plated myself.  I did not even mention the hard rice nor the lack of bell peppers.  The pork itself was pretty good. Once I got closer to the middle of the chop it seemed to me to be under cooked.  I asked the manager and she informed me that they cook their pork medium well. I asked if they could cook it for another minute or so. She said she could not due to covid but she COULD microwave it lol...which made no sense to me but ok. If you can take my plate/item back to the kitchen to microwave it why then can  you not just put in back on the grill or in a skillet.  At that point I just asked for a togo box and the check.  I live very close to this restaurant and was really looking forward to sharing it with my friends. We may still visit for wine but definitely not the food.
Amazing appetizers, great draft selection, and lovely staff
Love this place! Rustic look coupled with amazing wines and a delicious menu. Their charcuterie board is a must!
Attentive service, good food, nice wine and beer selection.
Everything was fine, drink , meals, defenetly we will be back !
a preferred evening place. the service was sociable and attentive.

Chicken was undercooked. Delivered to us cold. Then took it back to the kitchen to over cook it very dry . We just could choke down undercooked chicken. Wasn’t good and left a bad taste with us. Maybe on different day . Pretty expensive to leave disappointed.
Good beer selection. Decent food.b
Good place to relax and unwind.  The staff was friendly and sociable. The place has a great atmosphere. Feeling here is like a restaurant in Fort Worth I liked.

Nice staff and a good drink selection, but the food was disappointing. It could've been so good, and sounded delicious, but the food items were bizarre, tasted cheap, and some items weren't properly cooked.
Great drink selection and the pretzels and beer cheese are amazing!

I went here for dinner with a group of friends on a Thursday evening. The atmosphere inside was cozy. Tables were few due to Covid-19 which made the restaurant a little quiet but not terribly uncomfortable or awkward. Great service, very helpful with drink and food recommendations. Our food was delicious. I had the build-your-own charcuterie board. (The Ewephoria 12 month cheese was divine!) We really enjoyed our night out!

If you love cheese, charcuterie, and craft beer this is the place!  A somewhat eclectic-rustic vibe. Suggested this place for champagne toast and shareable plates for a kickstart to my friend’s bachelorette party-they all loved it! Perfect place for social drinks and dining.
Great atmosphere, the best service, and food to die for. We spend considerable time in St Louis after tonight's meal the Bridge will become a must have!!!
Horrible attitude and bad service.
Do not leave if it's busy, it is worth it. I've had nothing but enjoyable experiences here and plan to keep visiting.

Ambiance is excellent. Some seating outside. Great service. Wide wine and beer selection but no cocktail menu. My steak was overcooked and orzo lacked flavor. Hummus was unique but lacking in creaminess.
Beer and food were really good, inventive, and filling.  They might have some unusual beers in can or bottle that are no longer on the menu. Just ask!
Food, beer and service were all top notch! Thank you!
Delicious Cuban sandwich and drinks. They try to include local beer, spirits and wine.

First time here. Small quaint atmosphere for an intimate group or date night. Great selection of wine and beer. Both locally and nationally sourced. Food is excellent. Service is quick. Usually packed, but on a Sunday night not so much.
Mitch was an attentive and excellent server.  Great selection of drinks and delicious food!
Fun!!!
Soooooo good. Great atmosphere, wonderful waitress. Food was top notch. We will definitely be back!
Mitch is maybe the best bartender I have ever had. Between his knowledge and passion for the beer and the brand, he truly makes your experience a memorable. Great guy great place!

Amazing beers on tap and a Mitch the bartender knows his stuff! Has knowledge on all beers he is serving. Great experience and glad we came! Mitch could be the greatest person I have ever had, serving beer

First time in St Louis for a bLues game ! Our server Mitch Was amazing .. I did not have to pour my own wine at anytime, he was so attentive and on it, he made sure my glass was full always! Great food and service !
Great atmosphere for beer and wine enthusiasts! Enjoyed their wonderful food as well!
Great food and service!
Mitch is a champ!
Amazing food and excellent beer selection! Calm and quiet on a sunday afternoon. Highly recommend. Staff was warm and friendly.

Great beer selection. Pretzel rolls with beer cheese was good. The "daily special" shrimp gumbo had one piece of shrimp and two pieces of sausage, and the mound of rice in the middle was undercooked. Flavor was otherwise good. Nice atmosphere.
Great Cuban! Impressive draft list!!
Great food,wine,dessert and service
Great selection of beers. (Read: I wasn't in the mood for wine, but there was a good selection.)

Bridge Tap House & Wine Bar is a romantic restaurant where you can enjoy a charcuterie board paired with an extensive wine or beer selection. It is the ideal place to impress a special someone, or in my case, a co-worker who also enjoys awkwardly running on sidewalks in the dark to a restaurant a half-mile away. Despite our slightly sweaty ‘brows, they were kind enough to seat us at a candlelit table in their upper-level dining space. Although they have a “fancy” menu, there are so many options to choose from for both a custom charcuterie board or individual entrees, and I think most people will find their menu rather approachable. So whether you are trying to impress a new date or enjoy a post jog meal, this is a great place to enjoy a pint, glass, or various assorted meats and cheeses.

We pre gamed a little to hard before we got there so the waiter, Jeffery built us a charcuterie board then told us what told us what to order (the Carolina pork chop) .  We couldnt have been more happy!!  The food was sooo good and the atmosphere was really neat!
Good service
Great selection of beers on tap. Seems like a good wine and liquor selection, as well. I ordered the grapefruit salad for dinner, which was excellent. The bar manager was very knowledgable.

The bartender was super rude. Work in the service industry. First time not tipping anyone ever. But if you want to make your guests feel uncomfortable and like they are annoying the bartender, hire the blonde:)

My wife and I really enjoyed dinner here. We started with the Piatto Italio, which was a delicious charcuterie board. Then, she got the chicken & risotto, while I got the restaurant's take on a Cuban sandwich. Both were delicious - prepared well and very flavorful. We didn't imbibe, but had we desired, it appeared there were many excellent beer and wine options to choose from, including an extensive tap stocked with quality brews (a changing cast I'm sure, but just for example, I think I saw Founders, Southern Tier, Lagunitas, among many others).
Mediocre
Excellent beer selection! The atmosphere is incredibly warm an inviting. Very low key and not too loud. Cheers!

Went here for an anniversary dinner on new years day and it was a great find. Given the limited options of open restaurants on the holiday, we're so glad Bridge was! The dinner was delicious (get the grapefruit salad!) and for dessert we got the brie and chocolate board - amazing! Also very reasonably priced, nothing on the menu was over $20 and they were good sized portions.

I really like it here. They have a broad and tasty range of beers on tap. Bartender Jeff is very helpful and seems to always be there working hard. The food is also high quality and has lots of snack options to try. If you live downtown they also have fast pickup sandwiches

Updated:  Adding a star simply due to them taking the time to respond.  Our drink order was taken somewhat promptly however after waiting for drinks for what was much longer than it should have given how busy this place was we decided just to leave.  Found out later that they charged the party we were with $60 for the drinks we never received.  Who does business this way?

What a great first impression of St. Louis! I had the sirloin board and the spicy tomato jam mixed with the Danish blue, sliced sirloin, and peppery arugula layered on toasty slices was genius. The gumbo was good too, but it was the service and selection that elevated the establishment. Montana was knowledgeable and attentive. She made some great beer recommendations. I finished the night with one of the best Manhattans I have had in a long time!
Great little bar!

Love this restaurant! Very busy during the sports-ball seasons. The upstairs can get loud if the restaurant is full. GREAT beer selection and awesome shareable plates, plus nice entrees. The decor is quirky and cool.

A nice tap house and a bar. A great selection of beers, wines & cheeses and other cocktails. The service is reasonably fast and the staff is great. It’s quite busy most of the time, yet the service is timely. There are not many entrées to order from, but whatever was there, was tasty & good portions.
Amazing food, craft drinks, and customizable cheese boards. 5 star service. Must stop
Great vegan options!
Great beer selection
Great menus. fast service. Excellent ambience.

This is a place with an upscale environment and sensible prices. You can easily meet a group of friends here and have a great drink from either the beer, wine, or cocktail list and even a few bites to eat and not break a budget! However, you can also have a romantic dinner here and partake in having the higher priced items and still have a great night. A very nice and fun tap house and wine bar located in downtown.
Food was excellent as always.   Atmosphere was excellent as always.  Service lacked a little bit to be desired.
Chips are killer. Sandwich quality is unparalleled.  Big recommendation

Came from a Blues game and as a customer the blonde young girl that waited on me was one of the rudest young ladies to wait on me. She never made eye contact. Never felt welcome at all so went on to next bar.

Excellent dinner. My pasta was VERY HOT when it was served and stayed hot the whole time. Many times pasta dishes tend to cool but this was excellent.  My grandaughter had the pork chop on mashed potatoes. Wow. It was huge.  We tasted 3 Greek white wines, delicious!  They have a lovely variety of charcuterie boards to share. Great for a group.

If I could give 0 stars I would. Been there before and everything was excellent. Service this time was horrendous. My server didn't greet me when I sat down, took forever to take just my drink order and was clearly more focused on talking to her co-workers at the bar than doing her job. I wanted to order more food but the server couldn't be bothered to come back. When she gave me my appetizer she continued talking to the person next to me and just put my food on the bar. So frustrating. I finished my appetizer and went somewhere else.

At first look, the buffet seemed small but actually it had everything I wanted. There were two rice dishes, the staple tikka masala, tasty tandoori chicken, more meat dishes, lentils, saag, more vegetables, warm naan, and a variety of desserts. I was pleasantly surprised by the coconut soup and the masala chai which were both wonderful ways to cool down the spices in my mouth. I'll have to stop by again.
Piatto Italia board was my fav! Upstairs is quiet and clean.

I celebrated a birthday celebration here with my friends this past weekend and was told inaccurate information on how we would be accommodated. I get there and the host had the worst attitude and was rude and when mentioned that it was for a special occasion, it was not even once acknowledged it was that individuals birthday. We didn't get prompt service. The food was cold and was sent back. You expect a hot meal not cold one. Typically, people go for the experience of dining and good service for a special occasion and while not comparing this place to an Applebee's and have dined in finer settings for a special occasion where even a plate of dessert was brought not once did our server do that or better yet have checked on us in a more prompt manner. I will never recommend this place and I will never go back either. It is one of the slowest and poorest service I (we) have ever experienced. I'm sure Retreat Gastropub or other gastropub competitors would fare much better in service. Cake or no cake. Fine wine or no fine wine and expensive cheese and fancy risotto or not. Their host would have welcomed them rather than with an attitude and given them proper service. I wish I would have went to Rosalitas.

Very interesting and good flavors. We had three different cheese boards plus the pretzel balls. My fave was the orange jam and the pretzels. The focaccia bread was excellent. Wine was good. A bit more selection would be nice.  I thought it was a bit pricey. See photos and it was a $90 tab for 3 with 2 glasses of wine. I probably won’t return.
Mitch was super friendly. Our first visit but won’t be our last. Great place to relax on a Saturday afternoon.
I love it!! Amazing food, great atmosphere and our waiter was adorable. You should try it!

Interesting menu offerings. The appetizers were very good. Only downside, noise level was high. Hard surfaces on floors, walls, ceilings reflected sound. Everyone increased volume, increasing problem.
Food was great, wine was great, service was amazing!
Works for me. Menu is excellent, light choices or full entree. Cozy bar with great service. I’ll be back!
Excellent beer and wine. Thanks, Montana!

Fantastic cheese board options! Bartenders were great and gave good recommendations and were well informed. Good wine and beer options as well

We were visiting from out of town, and we tried it based of of proximity and reviews. The service, drinks, food, and atmosphere were all top notch. We will definitely be back on our next pass through St. Louis.
You absolutely will not be disappointed.
This place is truly pretentious, but it works. I think the drinks are overpriced, but I loved the charcuterie boards.
Great selection of beers. Montana is awesomeness. Highly recommended if you’re visiting the Arch or in St Louis looking for a great place to grab drinks and food.
Brandy was a wonderful waitress. Excellent ambiance and menu.

Extensive local and semi-local craft beer list, organized clearly by style. Wine list was a little limited comparatively but by no means bad! I’ve only ever eaten charcuterie or shareable plates so I can’t speak to the entrees but overall decent, if a bit pricey for portion size. Can be busy and full on popular nights and the space can be noisy - but overall a nice date spot!
Amazing atmosphere. We did wine flights and a charcuterie board. It was a great experience.
Build your own charcuterie board was amazing!
Good Beer & Wine selection and the food was really good too. Great place to enjoy association with friends for a quiet drink or meal. Highly recommended.
Good food and great staff. Don't expect standard versions of anything at this location.
Superb beer choices.  👍 Pickled fruit app was 🤢
A favorite of my wife - plenty of inebriators to pair with lovely food.

I visited this place cuz it had great reviews. However, my experience was not great.  The waiter was dry, and not helpful at all. Even worse, when I wanted to by wine by the bottle and asked to taste it, he said that they do not have open bottles! Lol!  We got wine by the glass; Rose and Pino. Both cheap brands but cost almost as much as the bottle itself in an alcohol store. Rose 4/10. Red 5/10.  Their cheese assortment was not great either. The waiter could not recommend any of them. Cheese 3/10.  Olives super salty and very soft. Not good for serving 2:10.  Will not visit again.
I first met her here 💛.
Bad and uncaring service. Food wasn’t much better.
Fun date with my love... great service and wonderful wine&cheese selections always a great experience
Wonderful selection of beer and wine!  Bison sausage had good flavor but was a bit dry.  Cool place!
The selection of inebriants allows for even the most ventured to have a unique drinking experience. The food is top notch, as well.
Don't miss out on this gem. Bartenders are friendly, and fun to talk to. Amazing beer selection. I'd drive 13 hours back to St. Louis just go to here again.

It was very nice. A bit pricey but the food is very well prepared and not your average fare. They also have a very nice beer list. The atmosphere is great, we sat outside in the shade of the buildings and the weather couldn't have been better. If eating outside isn't your thing the interior is very comfortable. The crowd is on the younger side but if you are a foodie or beer geek you'll fit in. Check em out.
All the wines. Get the custom charcuterie board. ❤️

Their drink selection is huge. Absolutely loved it. The Pad Thai entree, not so much. It tastes nothing how traditional Pad Thai tastes. I ordered some cinnamon pretzels for my app and those were superb. The nutmeg glaze gave it a fall season dessert feeling.
Fantastic beer selection and a solid food menu. Lots of charcuterie selections, as well as salads, sandwiches, and other options.
Great wine
Best bartender ever
Amazing beer selection. The cheeses are extraordinary and come with a generous amount of mixed nuts and bread.
Chicken Biscuits were the bomb! Long list of beers on tap!

My sister and I stopped by here before a concert at the Enterprise Center. Not only was our waitress super friendly, she made a point of getting us our food and wine in enough time for us to enjoy them before we left. I highly recommend the smoked striploin board. The wine was good (not too pricey) and we liked the freedom of being able to create our own charcuterie board. Will definitely visit again when we are back in town.
Great ambience. Wide selection of beer and wine! We did try a couple of cheeses, which were pretty good!

Just moved in across the street and this was the first place we went out to. Tons of taps with a bartender who knew about them all and was happy to walk you through the options and what and where they all came from. Only had snacks (the pretzel bites) but they were good. Will eventually try try more of the menu.
Our brie cheese board was great. All the wines we had were unique and on point. Good at atmosphere and a solid choice for anyone in a wine and cheese mood
Our service was lovely. Our food was delicious and very reasonably priced. Everyone I dined with enjoyed their meal.
Friendly service, great menu and beer selection.  The chocolate trio dessert was wonderful
Best taproom in downtown, and the food is top-notch.
Our server was very knowledgeable and friendly.
Great beer selection, desserts were really good
Great place to visit. Have enjoyed this place many times and will return.
Very unique place, such a classy bar, there are lots of variety wines.
Delicious food and wine.  I love this place and have for years.  There were a couple blunders this visit and the manager addressed both which shows their commitment to a quality experience.
Great selections for wine and beer.  Friendly, knowledgeable staff.  Fun place to finish out date night.
Pad Thai was to die for!
Nice ambiance,  and good service.  Nice tap selection, the food was what I based my rating on.  I liked it, but wouldn't go back unless I was already downtown.
Very good selection of beer.  Food is good but over priced.  8.00 for a cup of broth soup! You gotta be kidding!
The food was great. Beer choices vast and excellent. I had the fish dish and I loved it.
This place was amazing.  The grass fed steak was cooked to perfection, great draft selection.  Would definitely go back.

Cheese board was a little boring and uninspired. Drinks were way overpriced. A glass of scotch and a glass of wine plus a cheese board was $60. Service was so so. Staff seemed a little confused as to who was supposed to do what. It's a basic bar/restaurant that tries to be fancy and charges you for it.
Excellent place

You MUST try this place! I can't say enough good about it! Huge selection of beer, wine and fine whiskey! The menu offers amazing food selections and charcuterie boards! Try a charcuterie board, it is an experience all in itself!!

50+ beers on tap, a charcuterie menu that includes duck and bison, and a great bartender; what more can I ask for on a Saturday afternoon? I've been in town for about 30 hours so far and been here twice already. I only went between lunch and dinner, but it was a very chill spot to spend a couple of afternoons. They have 4oz pour option, so you can try a lot of beer on the cheap. If this place had a TV to watch the game I never would have left, but that's obviously not the vibe they're going for (which is totally okay).
Fabulous experience, delicious pairings tried new wines. Friendly service.definitely will go again when I'm in St Louis.
Great food, we did small plates. Excellent wine and beer selection. Montana was a great bartender!
A little pricey, but you get service you pay for, great choices that are sophisticated and high quality

My husband and I love this place! We live in Houston but everytime we are here visiting family we always have to make a stop here! Great tap list, and the best charcuterie selections. Always a must when we are in St.Louis!
great atmosphere, awesome selection of beer. it's a little higher class than what i usually go to. try not to break their tables, they will kick you out, speaking from experience. lol
Such a great atmosphere. Down to earth yet spohisticated.

It's a genuinely excellent place to wind down an evening. We sat at the bar, where service was EXCELLENT. It's never a problem to sample a beer before you buy one and our bartender Ryan was extremely knowledgeable and able to suggest several beers based on my particular tastes. Also got a cheese plate that was great. I would 100 percent go back next time I'm in town.
Very enjoyable

Great beer and wine. One hell of a meat cheese board! Our bartender/waiter was super knowledgeable in all aspects from the menu to the drinks.  He paired the meat and cheese board perfect for our drinks. If you want a low key, classy place to grab a drink or a lighter meal, this is your spot.
Good beer selection but the beer bottles gave me false hope that they had them. Turns out those are just past brews.
Bar food with good beer selection.

Great selection, but bartender didn't know much about numerous beers (recently updated beer menu they said). Good space inside with comfortably close quarters. I'd definitely go again if somebody invited me, but it's not the place I'd go by default.
Awesome find in STL
Excellent food and great beer and wine selection!
Nice atmosphere,  decent food, a little pricey.
Good selection 4oz to sample. Great food, nice service.
Great and extensive beer list. Tasty and interesting small plates. It's a great spot to share some small plates.
Quality eats, good service
Great bartender and great experience! They had an vast charcuterie selection and it was beyond delicious! Definitely try bison sausage and the riesling soaked apricots.
Very good beers and boards. Highly recommend the 3 dips with Olive Tapanade, Dill Onion, and Hummus. Each are delicious and don't make me pick
Good drinks, slow service.
Good drink selection, cool place. The food wasnt bad, just underwhelming.
Always a great selection here. Very nice place that never disappoints.
I haven't tried the food, but I enjoyed the ambiance and the large drink selection.
Stellar beer selection and the knowledge to explain.

Came for a late night meal and boy was I surprised! Yes the large beer selection and tasters (4oz for $2) was legit but if you come here you HAVE to try the Gjetost Mac & cheese because it is hands down the most exciting Mac & Cheese flavor I've had, EVER! Not only that, but it came with my club sandwich made of marinated chicken, sliced NY strip, and bacon! Like, whaaaaa!? 🤤
One of our top five places in the city.  Beer selection is great, food is wonderful, and the staff is exceptional.
I'm not a beer drinker but he is and was impressed with the selection. I had a delicious Old Fashion and the appetizer was perfect. I do recommend a visit.
A very hip, cozy place to eat and drink amazing wine/beer. The selection seems endless!
Nice decor
Excellent selection of beers and great good! 5 stars for the baked brie alone!!

Fun place! Extensive wine and craft beer lists. Food was terrific, the pear salad amazing! I had the sauv blanc and the barbera, both delicious. The service was spot on, quick and our waitress seemed to stop by our table just when we needed something. The cheese board was delightful, so many to choose from and a tasty dessert menu. I'm looking forward to returning to Bridge my next trip to St. Louis. I highly recommend this restaurant.
Too stuffy for me

Every time we go here, we wonder why we don't only eat here. They have, maybe not the biggest, but definitely the best-curated beer selection in the city. Everything I have eaten there is one of the best things I have ever eaten. The servers are always incredible, but our server yesterday (I think her name was Ann Marie) was a new level of amazing. Vegetarian-friendliness: high. We usually just get a cheese and olive board, but they have several vegetarian options on their menu.
Great place for unique,  delicious food. And to try a few craft beers or wine!
Delicious burger, great rotating draughts. Friendly staff.
Great music, good food, cozy atmosphere. #romantic
Nice atmosphere...not a gan of the overpriced food.  Especially since the food wasn't worth the price.
Best seafood in st pouis

This is a great bar in downtown St Louis. The food is great and the draft selection is amazing. It's one of the few places in downtown St Louis that I feel comfortable bringing people from out of town for a drink.

My rating was initially wrong. I am not sure why it was rated low.  This place is 5 start all the way.  My meal was outstanding.  The wine flight was delicious and a great value. We will be going back!
Great wine with a  cheese plate. Staff was very helpful.  I would go back.
Good food and a huge selection on tap.
It's a lovely place to take your friends are first date

We only had drinks while here but it was a nice place with lots of options. We were there very early so it wasn't crowded and the staff chatted with us while they got the place ready. Would definitely go back.
Good selection of beers, but the prezel appetisers we're really just bread balls.
The atmosphere was very nice. Customer service is superb. A little pricey but it's worth it
I have never been treated more rude by the staff at any restaurant/bar in my entire life.
Nice relaxing restaurant.   Food was good, Mac n Cheese and pasta was very good.  Service was good as well.  Chill, a little younger vibe.
Amazing beer selection and delicious food as well!
Nice fun place to visit.

Great wine and beer selection and a nice selection of cheeses. I hear the rest of the menu is also good! Service was also great and the waiter was really helpful. If I had more time in St Louis I would've gone back to try something from the main menu.
Awesome time, try and get Jeffrey as your server, great guy, amazing server!
Ok had a few beers

Fantastic!  We were too hungover to wait in line at the Rooster so we wandered down to the Bridge--no regrets! I love the Flower Power Beer Flight and the Baked Brie appetizer. If you get one thing while you're here, it better be the mac'n'cheese! Our bartender displayed the best service I've seen in a long time, and we wouldn't have selected our meals without his A+ input. I look forward to returning to Saint Louis just to eat here again!

what sold me is the custom charcuterie board, however it was a bit pricey. Need to add labels to the Cheese's on the board or the staff needs to be trained better so they can recognize the product when served. I should have been told what was what when it was set down in front of me. Would go back again
Staff was helpful and attentive. The Mac and cheese is maybe the best thing I’ve ever eaten in my life. I need their recipe. Beautiful place .
Great place. Yummy nibbles, excellent staff & cool, comfortable decor!
AMAZING service, tons of drink options, top notch food, and service unlike anything else. Highly recommend to anyone looking for a quick drink, date night, family gathering, or just a nice night out.
Very friendly staff and nice quiet bar
Amazing beer selection, great charcuterie, and great service.
Good food and tons of selections of beers and wine!
Cozy and interesting, with lots of beer and wine selections and delightful food. No TV's which makes me happy!
Best tap list and food in the city.
So glad we found this St. Louis gem. The duck charcuterie plate was amazing and the beer and wine selection was excellent. We will definitely stop there when ever we are in St. Louis
A great mix of wines and beers from local brews to imported sparkling wines.
Food is average.

We had a great experience tonight. Brandon was the best server!!! He was so knowledgeable about the pairings and drink suggestions. We had different ciders(raspberry and a beet cider), all kinds of beers (mo’wheato), and wonderful cheeses with focaccia, olives, apricots soaked in Riesling, cranberries, apples(with the best buttery cheese),  and mixed nuts plate. It was a little loud upstairs as it got crowded, but will definitely go back!!

Very tasty food, with large variety of tap beer and wine. My favorite was the Bailey's Ale and the Two Hearted Ale. Staff was helpful and very nice. Relaxing atmosphere in all. Excellent location in downtown. Wonderful experience.
Lovely spot in downtown. Lot's of beer on tap, good food with a nice atmosphere. Friendly service.
Great beverage selection! The Rainbow Trout was excellent! Definitely will return when I'm back in town.
Great Beer List!
Beautiful atmosphere, great service! Huge beer and wine menu! Food is delicious, but might be a bit fancy for some people.
(Translated by Google) Good variety of beers and nice atmosphere  (Original) Buena variedad de cervezas y lindo ambiente
Stopped by for a drink and small snack. Highly recommend the soft pretzels and beer cheese—they’re pretzel balls! Hummus was also delicious! Excited to try more of their food in the future.
Had great food and drinks at The Bridge Taproom tonight.  Our server, Brandon, made the night most fabulous! Would not have been the same without him!
Great beer selection and the server was knowledgeable about the differences.  The food was pretty good.
Huge selection of beers, great for an after work pint

Awesome food and great beer and wine.  True to advertising, "Serious Beer" <- only reason why we came.  Shout out to our server, David, who had great recommendations and made our visit awesome.  He also made great recommendations for places to see and eat as we were from out of town

Had the Duck charcuterie plate (again), duck sausage and duck breast. Amazing amount of cheese, meats and additional sides to choose from. Excellent beer and wine menu. Multiple visits have resulted in excellent experiences.
Great place to get a beer, Emily was a great bartender

Friendly staff. Easy to find. Parking was no problem. 57 beers on tap. Literally something for everyone.
Good food service can be inconsistent
Fabulous beer selection and the food was amazing. Highly recommend

Very nice place. Super friendly wait staff. The drink menu is a little limited, however there is something on the menu for everyone. They did a good job curatoring it. great wine selection great bourbon selection. I recommend it.
Good service, food and bar. On the expensive side, though

Awesome!!! The atmosphere is incredible, the food is delicious, and the beer selection is over the top. I love that you can make your own flight of most of the beers. Only complaint is I wish there was a larger selection of wine by the glass, there is pretty much one wine for each type of wine.

We always love to visit here as there is always something new to try and the staff is always very helpful and polite! The food is delicious as well and there is always new additions to keep it fresh. The atmosphere is so relaxed that you'll find yourself staring longer than anticipated which is always a good thing. Plus the building and decor is beautiful!

Beautiful building, friendly staff and amazing food! The cheese platter with olives as an extra side....amazing. We asked the bartender to choose a beer flight based on our likes and they nailed it. Great experience!
I get free alcohol and the taste of everything I had here was unpleasant compared to what I usually indulging
Good selection of beers, late night is fantastic and you'll get good service.  Exploring the charcuterie options is a must.
Great vibe, awesome service & great food

Came in for a late supper with friends. At least half the menu was not available (out of food). The Cuban sandwich was mushy and the server almost completely ignored us. He wasn't even curious as to why I only took 2 bites of a $13 sandwich. I'd never go back.
Awesome!
This little gem is an unexpected treat! a nice place to unwind and drink wine after a long hard work day... alright I would recommend it after a short easy work day too...
Outstanding food and the beer and wine list was all you could want. The duck charcuterie board was fantastic.
Great selection of beers, decent menu, cozy space
Really extensive drink selection and good salads. It's more formal than casual, but going before a game in St Louis gear is always fine too.

I have always been a big fan of this place! Been coming here for a couple years now. Always a delight. Today I got the roasted pair salad which is to die for, paired with a very nice apricot hefeweizen picked by Ashley the amazing bartender here today. I highly recommend coming here.

I love visiting Bridge.  Very unique tasty foods and a nice wine and beer menu.  Tou can get cheese and meat boards or full entrees.  We've had both and it is all delicious.  The wait staff is very knowledgeable and friendly also.
Enjoyed a private party here. Food was great and super selection of beer on tap!
Expansive wine and beer tap selection, definitely try the cheese plate selections, over 20 imported cheeses to choose from along with homemade focaccia & smoked meats.
Very eclectic menu and great service. The wine and beer selections are endless. Nice environment.
Amazing.
Expensive. Smaller portions but wide variety of beers. Great ambience.
Very nice wine selection and the food was delicious. I had the trout. Would highly recommend.
Amazing selection. Unique and great service.
Had a great meal and the beer selection was really good. Nice atmosphere.

In town for some vaca. Walked to this quaint, wine bar to relax. We each bought a bottle. Me Rioja, Linda a White Bordeaux. Me steak, her Cuban. Both spot on. Great atmosphere. Highly recommend. Thanks guys!
Terrific hospitality and really tasty food. An extremely healthy list of great beers and Delicious starters. The Cuba Missouri is fabulous!

Great service and food. They are also high donors for the DOFL. Can get a little hard to hear if alot of people are in there. Dining area mainly upstairs and restrooms located downstairs near the bar.
Good food and atmosphere. Small plates are a bit too small for a meal and the large plate are quite large. Easier to manage with at least three people with similar food tastes.
Great brunch today!

The service was terrible and that was the best part of the meal.  My girlfriend got the wrong dinner completely. The food was tasteless and since they consider themselves upscale with a chef they don't have salt and pepper at the tables. Everything but one person's sandwich was extremely bland. The beer and wine selections were outstanding but if you want to eat go somewhere else. It was a huge disappointment.
Great beer selection, service ok.  Left after 1 beer.
Great atmosphere, and great wine and beer selection.

Not a good place for dinner! The mac and cheese was soupy. I ordered from online and their menu was super out of date. The ingredients were fresh but that does not equate to good taste. I had the ny strip club and the chicken was extremely dry. I am assuming the high rating is mainly due to people's fixation with alcohol and longing for a sense of status. Because I ordered online I have no bias based on atmosphere, presentation, nor service. Buying freshing and putting it on a plate could be their thing...this establishment failed at cooking. But that is probably not their forte.
I love the atmosphere and the food is fantastic!  Great unique selections of charcuterie, wine and beer.
Awesome charcuteries and great entrees. Wine and beer menu are extensive!
Great beer selection and the food is a bit fancy but delicious.
Great beer selection. Good service on a busy night at the bar. Bartender was very knowledgeable and offered some great beer suggestions based on what I was drinking.

I got a wonderful vegan gluten free rice noodle, yellow curry dish.  I am going to try to recreate this at home so that I can share with my family. The tofu was so nicely flavor that it was a highlight of the dish.  This will be a challenge to duplicate! My coworker got a distinctly non-vegetarian sandwich which he said was really good. I will make a point to return should I find myself in St. Louis again.
Quaint, excellent service , great wine (moscato &  cabernet)!

The menu was intimidating but the waiter was super helpful and not condescending at all. We got to try new amazing food and the atmosphere was incredible. It was perfect for a date night. Photo is the table setting.
Had a really good time on a Monday afternoon here. Most of the people were from out of town but the drinks were good, priced fairly, and it was relatively quiet.
Bit dark, good food. Felt a little slow on service and was expecting server to know more about the wines when asking for recommendations.
Friday evening, there was just one bartender for the bulk of out time, delaying drink orders in general.  Their cheeses and meat were good, and the server was very professional and helpful.
Good food great drinks
Excellent beer selection.  Food is good but never surprising. Menu rarely changes and no specials (that I know of).
Outstanding food and extensive drink menu. A definite stop on every trip to St. Louis.
What a wonderful place to lose track of time and enjoy great company. Beverage and food selections to match the setting. Highly recommended!!!
Interesting menu well executed. Staff is friendly and knowledgable.

I've been to quite a few Bailey's establishments, as I used to work for the company (Rooster S. Grand). However, none of them have come anywhere close to the quality of food and service I experienced at Bridge. I sat at the bar, as I'm a bartender and it's my preferred place to sit. The bartenders were wholly knowledgeable in the beer and wine they serve, ready to make educated recommendations as needed, and were extremely fun to talk to. They really know how to make someone feel at home, which is a big plus. All the food came out perfectly cooked, presented well and was absolutely delicious. I had the soft pretzels as an appetizer and the NY Strip club for my entree, with the rosemary gorgonzola bacon bread pudding as a side. I still dream about that bread pudding - imagine your grandmother's holiday stuffing on steroids.  Bridge definitely changed my mind about the all-encompassing views I've had of Bailey's Restaurants since before and after my tenure working for them. 5/5, great experience.
Excellent food, wonderful service, up scale dining. Loved the variety of food and wine choices.
Appetizers and drinks/dessert excellent!  Our entrees (pasta) we're okay.  If we were here for just drinks and appetizers, 5 stars.  Service excellent as well.
Good food, friendly and knowledgeable service from sommelier-in-training, Becky. I'd definitely make it back. Trout and cheese cake
Great ambience. Small menu but food is excellent. Drinks and beer selection is extensive.
Great charcuterie boards, amazing selection of beers and wines. Keep an eye out for the specials, they never disappoint!
Great selection of beer.

OMG I had the best meal I’ve had in St. Louis here. I had the papardelle ragu, the bread with tomato jam, and the macaroni and cheese (one of the best and most unique I’ve ever had). They also have an incredible selection of seasonably rotating beers and you can choose from a variety of flight options so you get to try lots of things. I ended up with a flight of 4 and loved all so much I couldn’t even pick a favorite. This place is a great spot for a special dinner because it has really soft romantic lighting and a great location.
Loved it. Great bartenders
Fantastic food and atmosphere. My waitress Leah was fantastic, and very attentive. Would recommend the Mac and cheese!
Delicious food and good service. A nice trendy bar with great food and drink options.
The service was great, the menu was extensive, and the food was absolutely exceptional! We were there for a girl's night after work. It's a great place to go if you love wine and fancy cheese.
Great service and alcohol selection. Atmosphere is romantic and sophisticated. Read the menu by candlelight!
Fantastic menu and lunch choices.  Don't let the outside fool you.  Intimate lunch or dinner place.  Moderate price.  Fantastic food choices.
Fun food, great service and fabulous cocktails!
Amazing food and atmosphere! The staff was incredible as well!

Pretty cool place! We ordered a cheese plate and we loved it!! The Brie was perfect with the fruits and nuts. And the andouille sausage was perfect! The summer sausage with jalepino was pretty decent and so was the sage cheese.  We also ordered the roasted pork salad. It's not the kind of salad I usually go for, but it was pretty cool. The texture of the pork was perfect! Feta cheese isn't always my favorite on a salad, but there was some kind of sweet granola that helped to create the perfect flavor combo!  Overall, I wouldn't mind going back and trying new cheeses and meats and getting an even bigger cheese plate. I probably wouldn't get that salad again, be maybe I'd give one of their sandwiches a try!
Friendly service. The tap selection is fantastic. They were out of my friend's first two food choices, but we each found something we enjoyed.

In general, this is a great place for food and drinks.  I've been a few times, and will go back, however, at my most recent visit, there were tons of food flies hovering around our table, which was really gross, and one of the water glasses had lipstick on the rim, and it wasn't from anyone at the table, so it clearly hadn't been cleaned properly.  Maybe it was just a weird/off night for them.  Our waitress, was really apologetic about the water glass, and was friendly and informative with her suggestions, but it's hard to enjoy a nice night out with friends when their are fruit flies all over the place.
Delicious food and great wine and beer selection
Get. The. Fondue.
Best downtown bar,  plus my bff works here.  Get the paprika popcorn too. NY wine flight was surprisingly good
Good beers, good wine, interesting dishes, good ambiance, good prices.
Fabulous. Get the fondue. You re welcome.
The staff can really guide you to some AWESOME boards!  Don’t discount the 100% Petit Verdot wine or the Norwegian Gejost cheese!  Let that cheese melt on the roof of your mouth!
Love this place
Great bar tenders
Good beer and wine menu.  Chacutterie was almost perfect.  Nice space, will be back.
Many draft beer and wine options to chose. Really good staff. If you're more in the mood of drinking something in a nice place it's a really good option.
Cool place. Great atmosphere and delicious food! The staff was really nice and friendly and offered great suggestions! We will definitely be back.
Excellent food.
The Bordeaux Around the World flight was really fun. I ordered a cheese plate for my meal and was not disappointed. It was crowded and bustling, but the staff were attentive.
Great food choices. Good service. Open later in the evening than many surrounding restaurants.
Best beer choices I've seen in a bar setting I have ever seen. Great workers who are knowledgeable and personable.

Upstairs on the leather sofas, great place to meet and talk. Nice wine flight experience for friends, and authentic German non-alcoholic beer for me. Best I've tasted. Good cheese and charcuterie boards with yummy bread and Cuban sandwich. Mood music without moody clients. Very hip but upscale. We hung out for several hours and had the lounge area to ourselves. Felt like someone's guest parlor, but someone so cool, I've never met them.
Grrat tapas
Great place, good people.
So I love this place! Food delicious, with many gluten free options, including house made bread! Our server Andrew was so knowledgeable about all our questions and even suggested a marvelous wine.

Great food (and gluten free, GF bread made fresh) and Andrew was very helpful in a quaint, stylish, relaxed atmosphere. Journeyman Last Feather rye old fashion followed by Lamb bolognese really hit the spot. My wife had a gluten free Saigon curry noodles; delicious. GF bread with olive tapenade just to round things out, was taken home as a snack. A must try.
good food and nice atmosphere in a cozy environment
The food was delicious and not overpriced. The wine and beer list were extensive. If you couldn't find something you liked there was something wrong! The service was superb!

Nice location in downtown St Louis. Swift & friendly service & a really great meal as well. I had the pan roasted duck breast that was prepared perfectly, medium rare of course. A must visit when in the gateway to the west!  10/17/17 - What …

Always a great experience. We had a group of 8 and the wait staff handled everyone's checks well.  The cheddar crisps are amazing.  The beer and wine selection is good and we appreciated the ability to order beer by 4oz, 12oz, 16oz, and 20oz.
Priced higher than reward. Ordering the Bloody Mary bar includes enough vodka for 2-3 drinks.
Great place, good vibes
Local atmosphere with a new age feel. Great food and HUGE selection of beer and wine
Very cool! Great beer selection. Another great Bailey establishment.
Selection of beer was great, and the prices really weren't too bad. However, service was not very good when we were there. Maybe they were short-staffed that night.

The staff is super friendly. Our waiter, Victor, was helpful while my boyfriend and I celebrated our 2nd year anniversary. He explained the menu to us and answered any questions we had. There are affordable prices considering the atmosphere. Overall, a great place to go for a romantic evening!

tacos were really good, beer sampler had some really interesting beers and a nice variety, overall service was really nice.  OH! and the best bread and butter pickles I have had in the pickle platter app.
Loved this restaurant. Great drink selection, delicious food, and loved the ambiance.

Met some co-workers after work.  Grabbed a beer and chat awhile.  What really impressed me is when we decided to get some food.   I got the grilled cheese with tomato bisque, and I have never been so impressed with a grilled cheese.  It was amazing!

We had the most lovely evening here. The food was amazing. We had their blue cheese pre-selected board. My boyfriend was raving about it the whole day after. Also, the entrees were perfectly seasoned and portion sizes were generous. There …
Good atmosphere, wine list and beer list, and creative menu. Would recommend and go back if staying downtown.
The food was fantastic. The selection of brews was staggering.

Great food and great drink selection. It doesn't matter if you prefer beer, wine or liquor - everyone will be happy. Only reason I'm giving it 4 stars and not 5 is how long it took to get our food. The place was slammed on an off night due to a conference and eclipse travelers but those are things that can be planned for...
Really great beer selection, good food, and helpful staff. We came here for lunch and had a great time.
The food was amazing!  The beer selection was pretty good as well.
Best spot to grab a beer and chill

This place has the best charcuterie and cheese boards I've ever had. The wait staff was very friendly but I think they actually forgot about us. It took us exactly 2 hours to get our entrees. It was a very busy night, but still wasn't a great evening. The entrees were lackluster as well.
I just wish they had large ICE Cubs for my rye. Other then that, the duck liver and the lamp tacos were delicious

(Translated by Google) 57 draft beers that can be served in four different sizes (4, 12, 20 and 64 Oz). Can you ask for more? If you like beer, don't miss it  (Original) 57 cervezas de barril que pueden servirse en cuatro tamaños distintos (4, 12, 20 y 64 Oz). ¿Se puede pedir más? Si te gusta la cerveza, no te lo pierdas
The food and server were both fantastic. My boyfriend and I highly recommend the grilled cheese!
Incredible food and wine! Visiting from Milwaukee, and truly impressed by the quality and quantity of the dishes/wine we ordered.
Everything that's hard to find is at Bridge.  Wow!  Awsome and affordable :)
It was absolutely delicious and the staff was awesome! Be sure to get the baked Brie.
good variety. 4oz pours are great. Pretzels were wonderful. Very reasonable prices.
Delicious, reasonably priced, and kitchen doesn't close till 11pm.
Great ambiance

Great restaurant! Cool little front tucked in on Locust. Your eyes immediately draw to the extensive beer and wine selection accessed by rolling ladder behind the bar and the massive tree branch chandelier. Food was very tasty accompanied by our wonderful server, Victor. Will be back again and happily recommend to others!
Ask for Victor he is amazing at choosing your wine and cheese platters

I live a few blocks from Bridge and stop by about once a week.  Extremely high level of customer service here.  For example, I ordered a sour beer (they usually have 5 or 6 on tap!) and the server thought it wasn't filled enough.  Without prompt they offered to bring me a smaller pour to make up for it.  I love it when a business notices a shortcoming and instantly makes it right without being asked.  I highly recommend this place!  They serve food late too!
Great beer menu, good food, and friendly staff.
Great service, food, and beer/wine/cocktails
Good service, good food
Trendy, loud, expensive. Great beer menu. Wine menu was limited but had some good offerings.
Great waiter, numerous selections
This place is awesome! We always put together a cheese and meat tray. We love it!
Hipster wine/cheese and craft beer bar. Attentive staff, nice selection on the beer/wine/cheese. Limited seating downstairs, more up
One of the best wine and beer menus in the city. Only had cheese and meat tray but it was great. Fun atmosphere.
Excellent food. Very upscale menu but at reasonable price. Very comfortable atmosphere and the wait staff was excellent. Fantastic beer and wine selection.
Good food, good cheese, beer and wine selection
Nice place. A Planet Fitness member invited me and I am really glad I came. Great service.

Very cozy place. The lighting is very dim but the atmosphere is very nice and welcoming. The service is great. The food is delicious and season very well. The drinks are well made. The whole experience was very enjoyable will come back again!

I can't give any feedback about the food since I only had a martini, but if the service and hospitality are any reflection then it has to be amazing!  I had a little bit of time to kill before catching my Amtrak back to Dallas, had just come off of four days of cycling on the Katy Trail, and wanted a martini which is how I found this place. Long story short, they opened their doors, let me bring my bicycle in, and even found a special spot in the neighboring gallery for it. I offered to change clothes (I was still my cycling gear on), and they told me they didn't care about that! I sat at the bar, was given a tasty beverage, and amazing customer service from all of the staff.  Thank you so much for your hospitality!
Service was very slow. Waitress ignored a few tables. In fact two other tables left without ordering due to slow service. Price was high and portions very small.
Nice little quaint drink and eatery on locust. Huge beer selection and very attentive staff. Sat on the front patio and our server was very kind and knew the menu. 5 stars for sure.
Food is very good, great selection of IPA's to choose from.  Service was very good and personable.
Cool place unique mix of elegance and casual. Good food from sandwich to entre. The house chips are very tasty.
Fantastic. Get the lamb tacos and the brie!
Great little wine and beer bar with eclectic by the glass selection. Visited St. Louis from out of town and this was a quaint oasis within blocks of most downtown hotels. Good food as well!
Good food, however, it gets really noisy because it is not a very big space

It's a little expensive, but the price is mostly justified. The beer selection is nothing to scoff at. Great place to go for something upscale, but not extravagant. Think around 50 dollars per person after appetizer, drink and entree.
Excellent selection at bar and food is very tasty.
Super cute wine bar with amazing food and service! Definitely somewhere to check out!!

Visited twice, had an AMAZING experience the first time and a less than stellar experience the second time. The first night our waiter spent time explaining wines and cheeses and making wonderful recommendations. He receives a 10/10. The second night our waitress was very cold and sharp with us. It was not a pleasant experience. It felt like we were an inconvenience to her. Drinks that were available the night before we're suddenly not: "I don't have that" she said " I don't have any of those". She receives a 4/10 or less.  If we hadn't have had such an amazing experience the first night, I would have not recommended this place to anyone. If the wait staff is good, the selection and recommendations are fantastic and the cheese platter is an experience all its own.

If you came to St Louis for some beer tasting and want some beers after all the breweries have closed then get here. 47(?) Beers on tap and a great selection. Like someone took the time to pick them out. Really great. If i lived in St Louis i'd be here all the time. Awesome place. Great grilled cheese. Great changing beer list. Staff extremely helpful. Go here.
Superior beer selection and excellent atmosphere
Really good food and drink selection
Beer heaven!
Great food. Awesome selection of beer and wine. Knowledgable staff
